                <note rend="inline" type="source">Doc. No. 13 bis (G).</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Amendment Proposed to the Clauses of the Draft Treaty
                        Concerning Bilateral Treaties</hi> (Art. 37.)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-08-20T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 37</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Each Allied or Associated Power will notify Italy, within a period of 6
                        months of the coming into force of the present treaty, which pre-war
                        bilateral treaty it <hi rend="italic">does not</hi> desire to keep in force
                        or revive.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">All treaties so notified are to be regarded as
                            abrogated</hi> within <hi rend="italic">one month from the date of
                            notification</hi>.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Any provisions <hi rend="italic">in treaties not so notified</hi>, which
                        are not in conformity with the present treaty, shall be deleted.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>All treaties <hi rend="italic">not</hi> so notified will be registered
                        with the Secretariat of the United Nations in accordance with Article 102 of
                        the United Nations Charter.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
